k=0
pn
 (x+y)^{pn} = \sum_{k=0}^{pn}\binom{pn}{k}x^ky^{pn-k} = \sum_{k=0}^{pn}\frac{(pn)!}{k!(pn-k)!}x^ky^{pn-k} = \sum_{k=0}^{pn}\frac{pn\cdot\ldots\cdot(pn-k+1)}{k!}x^ky^{pn-k} = \sum_{k=0}^{pn}p\frac{n\cdot\ldots\cdot(pn-k+1)}{k!}x^ky^{pn-k} = x^{pn}+y^{pn}, 
\;1\le k\le p^n-1\;
p\mid\binom{p^n}k
